This was very simple and quick to prepare. I sauted about a 1/4 cup of red onion (sliced lengthwise in strips) and added 2 cloves of garlic, the results were quite good. As a vegetarian, I served this as my main dish with sliced grape tomatoes over a bed of brown rice which even my meat and potato boyfriend enjoyed.

