Rating: 3
I made this with some multi-colored chard I found at our local super market. I added a little diced red pepper for color, and a squeeze of lemon at the end. Excellent accompaniment to fish (I served it with a roasted sea bass, sweet potato gnocchi, balsamic-red wine reduction, and a drizzle of basil-infused olive oil atop the fish, just for kicks). I have also mixed this recipe with pasta, a little more olive oil, and some prociutto.